ANTsRNet 1.0
  • Reference

3-D implementation of the "NoBrainer" U-net architecture

createNoBrainerUnetModel3D.Rd

Creates a keras model implementation of the u-net architecture avaialable here:

createNoBrainerUnetModel3D(inputImageSize, numberOfOutputs = 1,
  numberOfFiltersAtBaseLayer = 16, convolutionKernelSize = c(3, 3, 3),
  deconvolutionKernelSize = c(2, 2, 2))

Arguments

inputImageSize

Used for specifying the input tensor shape. The shape (or dimension) of that tensor is the image dimensions followed by the number of channels (e.g., red, green, and blue).
numberOfOutputs

Number of segmentation labels.
numberOfFiltersAtBaseLayer

number of filters at the beginning and end of the 'U'. Doubles at each descending/ascending layer. Default = 16.
convolutionKernelSize

3-d vector defining the kernel size during the encoding path.
deconvolutionKernelSize

3-d vector defining the kernel size during the decoding.

Value

a u-net keras model

Details

https://github.com/neuronets/nobrainer/blob/master/nobrainer/models/unet.py

Examples


# Simple examples, must run successfully and quickly. These will be tested.

library( ANTsRNet )
library( keras )

model <- createNoBrainerUnetModel3D( c( 128, 128, 128, 1 ) )
url <- "https://github.com/neuronets/nobrainer-models/releases/download/0.1/brain-extraction-unet-128iso-weights.h5"
weightsFile <- "nobrainerWeights.h5"
download.file( url, weightsFile )
model$load_weights( weightsFile )

print( model )
